kirc
====

kirc (KISS for IRC) is a tiny IRC client.

Install
-------

Building and installing from source.

    $ git clone https://github.com/mcpcpc/kirc
    $ cd kirc
    $ make && make install

Usage
-----

Only a nickname needs to be specified to connect. Consult
the manpage for a full list and explanation of available
arguments and default values.

    kirc [-s hostname] [-p port] [-c channels] [-r realname]
         [-u username] [-k password] [-h] <nickname>

Command Aliases
---------------

    <message>          send PRIVMSG to the current channel
    @<dest> <message>  send PRIVMSG to a specified dest.
    /<command>         send raw command to the IRC server
    /#<channel>        assign new default message channel
    /$                 toggle the channel filter on/off

Key Bindings
------------

Control keys map to natural key bindings find in other text
editors.

    CTRL+B  move the cursor one character to the left.
    CTRL+F  move the cursor one character to the right.
    CTRL+E  move the cursor to the end of the line.
    CTRL+A  move the cursor to the start of the line.
    CTRL+U  delete the entire line.
    CTRL+C  force quit kirc.

Bugs and Issues
---------------

Please submit via Github.

References
----------

* https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc1459.html
* https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc2222.html
